'''Wehọmẹ Alavọ Ayimatẹn Awọnlin Tọn''' (''Glẹnsigbemẹ: '''Lagos State University''''') also known as LASU, is located in Ojo, a town in Lagos State, Nigeria. The university was established in 1983 by the enabling law of Lagos State,[5][6] for the advancement of learning and establishment of academic excellence; its motto being For Truth and Service.[7] The university caters for over 35,000 students
